## Collecting the Debt

Instead of freezing the browser, we use `.then()` directly on the Promise ticket.

We say: "Hey JavaScript, go ahead and keep running the rest of the website code without waiting. But **.then()** when you finally get the data from the background, run this specific callback function!"

```javascript
// Fake network request that returns a Promise ticket!
downloadUserData()
  .then(function(realData) {
    // This only fires 5 seconds later!
    console.log("File finished downloading: ", realData);
  })
  .catch(function(error) {
    // If the internet completely crashed, run this!
    console.log("Failed! ", error);
  });
```
